## Framework-Specific Hook Recommendations

| Framework | Primary Hook Type | Secondary | Tone |
|---|---|---|---|
| Budget Warrior | Surprising stat | Curiosity gap | Confident, data-driven |
| Contrarian Takedown | Provocative question | Surprising stat | Thoughtful challenger |
| Underdog Champion | Curiosity gap | Story | Underdog advocate |
| High-Stakes Scenario | Scenario/story | Authority claim | Serious, high stakes |
| Legacy Justification | Story | Provocative question | Respectful, nostalgic |
| Tier List | Curiosity gap | Cold open | Analytical, fair |
| Myth Buster | Provocative question | Surprising stat | Investigative |
| Evolution Timeline | Cold open | Surprising stat | Historical, analytical |
| Head-to-Head Duel | Provocative question | Cold open | Fair referee |
| Golden Age Legacy | Story | Provocative question | Respectful, curious |
| Industry Shakeup | Surprising stat | Curiosity gap | Breaking news energy |

---

## Key Rules for Firearms Content Hooks

1. **NEVER attack the benchmark IN the hook** — respect it, then challenge it with data later
2. **Be specific** — "one specific test" not "the data says"
3. **Match the title** — hook must deliver on what the thumbnail/title promises
4. **NO self-intro** — skip "Hey guys welcome back", jump straight to the hook
5. **Authority is secondary** — mention testing methodology briefly, don't lecture
6. **Fair tone** — "raised the bar" not "destroyed" / "humiliated"
